Notes: No available ontology path matches a technical row identifier; this field is likely an internal database artifact used for tracking and should not be mapped to the clinical ontology.

‘patient_id’ is a pseudo-identifier for the patient. Path 1 brings us to Patient, but path 23 extends further to PatientIdentifier, which is a more precise semantic fit. There are no further, more specific 2-hop paths for PatientIdentifier.

‘diagnosis_code’ refers to a coded representation of the problem or condition. Path 5 (hasCode) is the base representation. There are 2-hop paths from Code (paths 66-68), but those are for details about the code (system, identifier, name), not the code value itself. Thus, path 5 is the most direct and semantically correct.

‘created_at’ represents the time at which the condition record was created. Path 17 (hasRecordDateTime) directly captures the record creation time. Other available dateTime paths (14, 16) refer to event or onset times, but not the record creation.

‘org_code’ identifies the institution providing the data. Path 8 (hasDataProviderInstitute) is a one-hop to DataProviderInstitute, but path 79 continues to its code, which is the semantically appropriate match for an organization code.

‘org_name’ is the human-readable name of the data provider institute. Path 8 (hasDataProviderInstitute) is a one-hop, but path 81 further specifies the organization’s name property, which is the most semantically precise.
